  "local_port": 60596,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get 95%+ in Class 12th Boards? What reference books can I use for it?",
  "response": "Achieving a 95% or higher score in your Class 12th Board exams requires a strategic approach, consistent effort, and the right resources. Here are some tips and suggested reference books to help you reach your goal:\n\n### Tips for Achieving 95%+\n\n1. **Understand the Syllabus and Exam Pattern:**\n   - Thoroughly review the syllabus for each subject.\n   - Familiarize yourself with the exam pattern, marking scheme, and question types.\n\n2. **Create a Study Schedule:**\n   - Develop a realistic and balanced study timetable.\n   - Allocate more time to subjects or topics where you need improvement.\n\n3. **Quality Over Quantity:**\n   - Focus on understanding concepts deeply rather than cramming information.\n   - Use active learning techniques such as summarizing, teaching others, or making flashcards.\n\n4. **Practice Regularly:**\n   - Solve previous years' question papers and sample papers.\n   - Take regular mock tests to simulate exam conditions and assess your preparation.\n\n5. **Revision is Key:**\n   - Regularly revise what you have studied to reinforce learning.\n   - Use spaced repetition techniques to enhance memory retention.\n\n6. **Seek Help When Needed:**\n   - Don\u2019t hesitate to ask teachers or classmates for help if you\u2019re struggling with a topic.\n   - Consider joining study groups or online forums for additional support.\n\n7. **Healthy Lifestyle:**\n   - Ensure you get enough sleep, eat well, and take short breaks to maintain focus.\n   - Engage in physical activities to keep stress at bay.\n\n### Recommended Reference Books by Subject\n\n#### Physics:\n1. **NCERT Physics Textbook for Class 12** - Essential for covering the entire syllabus.\n2. **Concepts of Physics by H.C. Verma** - Excellent for building a strong conceptual understanding.\n3. **Problems in General Physics by I.E. Irodov** - Great for advanced problem-solving.\n4. **Fundamentals of Physics by Halliday, Resnick, and Walker** - Useful for detailed explanations and practice problems.\n\n#### Chemistry:\n1. **NCERT Chemistry Textbook for Class 12** - Fundamental resource.\n2. **Organic Chemistry by O.P. Tandon** - Comprehensive for organic chemistry.\n3. **Physical Chemistry by P. Bahadur** - Good for physical chemistry problems.\n4. **Inorganic Chemistry by J.D. Lee** - Useful for inorganic chemistry concepts and practice.\n\n#### Mathematics:\n1. **NCERT Mathematics Textbook for Class 12** - Must-have for all topics.\n2. **Mathematics for Class 12 by R.D. Sharma** - Excellent for practice and understanding concepts.\n3. **Problems Plus in IIT Mathematics by A. Das Gupta** - Useful for challenging problems.\n4. **Objective Mathematics by S.K. Goyal** - Great for quick revision and practice.\n\n#### Biology:\n1. **NCERT Biology Textbook for Class 12** - Essential for foundational knowledge.\n2. **Trueman's Elementary Biology by K.N. Bhatia and M.P. Tyagi** - Good for detailed explanations and diagrams.\n3. **Biology by Pradeep's Publications** - Comprehensive with a focus on practice questions.\n4. **Objective Biology by Dinesh** - Useful for multiple-choice questions and quick revision.\n\n#### English:\n1. **Wren and Martin's High School English Grammar and Composition** - Essential for grammar and composition.\n2. **Exam Idea English Core for Class 12 by Madhukar Kumar Bhagat** - Good for practice papers and tips on writing.\n3. **CBSE All in One English Core Class 12 by Arihant Experts** - Useful for covering the entire syllabus and practice.\n\n### Additional Tips for Using Reference Books:\n- **Start with the basics using the NCERT textbooks.**\n- **Use other reference books for in-depth study and practice.**\n- **Regularly assess your progress by solving problems from various sources.**\n\nBy following these tips and utilizing these resources effectively, you can significantly improve your chances of scoring 95% or higher in your Class 12th Board exams. Good luck!",
